column5: Hi all,  Finally got out fishing again, manged a few hours early Sunday morning....fun times.    FATHER'S DAY FISHING  <object width="425" height="344"><param name="movie" value="
Awesome video Simon!!!  Good job on the Limey challenge Such a great fishery you have up there Keep up the great work and thanks for sharing!!! Jacques
Ha Ha awsome Limey! Yer needs a gurt net man. Gotta show this one to my son

Great report & video Simon,I know that wasn't the Goon,I,m guessing Thunder. I thought you might have been in the Walleye Masters this past weekend.With your talent,you might have brought home the BIG $$$.
awesome video simon worth the wait to get out fishing
Keep the videos coming! I am enjoying them tremendously!

Thanks Jacques, the only real challenge recently is 'Limey' finding time to fish!    darn....you guessed right...my secret is out!  A lot of people asked why i was not in the Walleye masters...my excuse...no live well.....lol...the real excuse....i dont know where the big fish are on the goon yet...and i dont want to pay a $300 entry fee to prove i dont know...lol.    Thanks corvette, yup...it certainly made up for the lack of fishing recently...mind you i would have settled for no fish too....just being out in the boat on a beautiful morning (by myself) was worth the wait.    Thanks Bill...the bass were on fire...but i was already an hour late so had to draw on every ounce of will power to drag myself away from a hot topwater bite and get home reasonably on time and actually be a father on Father's Day.    Thanks JB...will do!
Great video Simon. Love the POV angle, felt like I was there with you. Great morning on the water.

Thanks Simon for posting the video.  Always fun to watch your videos.  Pretty soon you will have the sponsors wanting to advertise themselves in your segments!  I'm surprised Rapala hasn't come after you for all of the success with the jiggin rap!
Very cool vid.  I do the same with my Vex.  Always fun.
